  <span id="freeText15441181714164835090" style="display:none">Finished 3 October 2018 and 4🌟🌟🌟🌟! <s>Review comments tomorrow</s>.<br /><br />How good it is to re-read a book and see (listen to) it through older, wiser, probably less jaundiced eyes (ears)! Reading some Gr friends' reviews of "The Lincoln Lawyer", I was quickly made aware that my 3 stars rating in 2009 or 2011 or whenever it was, might well have misjudged Michael Connelly's first Mickey Haller novel. Listening to the audiobook this week, I remembered barely a word of my first reading (except that his office was the back seat of a Lincoln Town Car), and I might well have been listening to it for the first time!<br /><br />Thank you to my friends who encouraged me to pick it up a second time. I enjoyed it so much I had to hunt through my audiobooks and see what my thoughts have been on other Mickey Haller novels. Harry Bosch #18 "The Crossing" is also listed as #6 Mickey Haller "The Crossing" and I have 'read' this one, but the good news is that I own Mickey Haller #5 "The Gods of Guilt" and I haven't listened to it yet! So it now on the iPhone and I have already started it.</span>
